com.miuey.happytree.annotation

Annotation Type Id


  • @Documented
@Target(value=FIELD)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Id
    Represent an identifier of an object of a class that represents a linear node with a tree behavior that will be transformed by HappyTree API.

    This id must be unique when a collection of objects that will be transformed into a real tree hierarchical structure is passed through of a tree session initialization.

    This happens because an object (declared with @Tree annotation) that will be transformed through API Transformation Process will represent, respectively, a node in a tree concept. So, each node in a tree must have a not null id and an unique id.

    Example: 
            public class TreeNode {
                @Id
                private String index;
                private String parentIndex;
 
                private String anyAttribute;
                ...
        }
